# Project Rules — Read DESIGN.md Before Every Edit

## CRITICAL: Preservation-First Approach
This project has an existing layout and structure that MUST be preserved.
DESIGN.md defines the visual refinement layer — not a redesign.
Your job is to IMPROVE what exists, not rebuild it.

## Current Architecture
- Next.js app router project (TypeScript + TSX)
- Styling: single `globals.css` file (no CSS modules, no Tailwind)
- CSS variables on `:root` drive all theming
- Layout: CSS Grid with `--dashboard-rail` for two-panel structure
- Components in `components/` (navigation/, jobs/, operators/, profile/)
- Key layout file: `app/layout.tsx`
- Key nav component: `components/navigation/workspace-header.tsx`

## What Must NOT Change
- The two-panel grid: `.dashboard-workspace` with `.today-rail` + `.queue-column`
- The header grid: `.site-header` column structure and responsive breakpoints
- The screening row structure: `.screening-row`, `.screening-summary-grid`, `.screening-actions-bar`
- The sidebar blocks: `.today-block`, `.today-stats`, `.today-apply-next`, `.today-resume-status`
- All responsive breakpoints at 1180px, 900px, and 720px
- The `--dashboard-rail` and `--site-gutter` sizing logic
- All component file structures and HTML semantics

---

## STEP-BY-STEP VARIABLE REMAPPING

### :root — Replace These Variables

**Fonts** (swap Public Sans → IBM Plex Sans, Geist Mono → IBM Plex Mono):
```
OLD: --font-display: "Public Sans", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
NEW: --font-display: "IBM Plex Sans", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;

OLD: --font-body: "Public Sans", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
NEW: --font-body: "IBM Plex Sans", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;

OLD: --font-mono: "Geist Mono", "SFMono-Regular", "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
NEW: --font-mono: "IBM Plex Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
```

**Colors** (tighten palette to DESIGN.md):
```
KEEP: --bg: #ffffff;
OLD:  --text: #111111;           → NEW: --text: #000000;
OLD:  --muted: #6a6a6a;          → NEW: --muted: #525252;
OLD:  --line: #111111;           → NEW: --line: #000000;
KEEP: --line-soft: #d6d6d6;      (close enough to #E5E5E5 — OR change to #e5e5e5)
OLD:  --line-faint: #ececec;     → NEW: --line-faint: #e5e5e5;
KEEP: --surface-soft: #f5f5f5;

ADD:  --accent: #D4E700;
ADD:  --accent-hover: #BFD100;
```

**@font-face** (replace both declarations):
```
OLD: font-family: "Public Sans" → NEW: font-family: "IBM Plex Sans"
OLD: font-family: "Geist Mono"  → NEW: font-family: "IBM Plex Mono"

Update src paths to point to the IBM Plex font files in the project.
If using variable font: IBMPlexSans-VariableFont_wdth,wght.ttf
If using static: load Regular (400), Medium (500), SemiBold (600), Bold (700), Light (300).
For Mono: load Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold static weights.
```

---

## COMPONENT-BY-COMPONENT REFINEMENT MAP

### Navigation — `.site-header`

**App title — `.site-brand strong`**
```
CURRENT: font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.22rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
TARGET:  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
```
Rationale: App title uses Plex Mono to distinguish it from content. Smaller, tracked, mono — reads as a system label.

**Nav tabs — `.site-workflow-link`**
```
CURRENT: font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; text-transform: none;
TARGET:  font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
```

**Active tab — `.site-workflow-link[aria-current="page"]`**
```
CURRENT: background: var(--surface-soft);
TARGET:  background: var(--accent); color: var(--text);
```

**Tab hover — `.site-workflow-link:hover`**
```
KEEP: background: var(--surface-soft);  (this is fine)
```

**Tab count — `.site-workflow-count`**
```
CURRENT: font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
TARGET:  font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
```
Minor tweak — keep mostly as is.

**Profile indicator — `.site-profile-link`**
```
CURRENT: font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; text-transform: capitalize;
TARGET:  font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
```

**Profile label — `.site-profile-label`**
```
CURRENT: background: var(--text); color: var(--bg);
TARGET:  background: transparent; color: var(--text); border: 1px solid var(--text);
```
This is the key change: profile switches from filled black to outlined/ghost.

**Profile label hover — `.site-profile-link:hover .site-profile-label`**
```
CURRENT: background: #2a2a2a;
TARGET:  background: var(--text); color: var(--bg);
```
Hover inverts to filled state.

**Profile mark — `.site-profile-mark`**
```
CURRENT: background: var(--surface-soft); border-left: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);
TARGET:  background: transparent; border-left: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
```
Or remove `.site-profile-mark` entirely if it's just a decorative spacer — flag for review.

---

### Sidebar — `.today-rail`

**Section labels — `.panel-label`**
```
CURRENT: font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; text-transform: capitalize;
TARGET:  font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
```
Switch from mono to sans-serif. Apply DESIGN.md Label style.

**Section titles — `.today-block-heading h2`**
```
CURRENT: font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
TARGET:  font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0;
```
Slightly smaller, semibold instead of bold. Cleaner.

**Stat labels — `.today-stats dt`**
```
CURRENT: font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.82rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; text-transform: capitalize;
TARGET:  font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
```

**Stat values — `.today-stats dd`**
```
CURRENT: font-size: 1.12rem; font-weight: 600;
TARGET:  font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 400;
```
Stat numbers switch to Plex Mono for data texture.

**Sidebar dividers — `.today-block + .today-block`**
```
CURRENT: border-top: 1px solid var(--line-soft); (already correct)
KEEP AS IS.
```

