## Global Typography Normalization

After remapping individual components, ensure these global rules:
- `h1, h2, h3` line-height: change from `0.98` to `1.15` (current value is too tight)
- All `letter-spacing: -0.03em` on headings → change to `0` (no negative tracking below display size)
- All `text-transform: capitalize` → change to `text-transform: uppercase` (labels should be full uppercase, not capitalize)
- All `font-weight: 700` on elements below 32px → change to `font-weight: 600` (reserve 700 for display/app title)

---

## Edit Discipline
- When editing globals.css, work section by section. Do not batch the entire file.
- After each section edit, list exactly what selectors and properties changed.
- Confirm that no layout properties (display, grid-template-columns, gap, padding that affects layout) were modified.
- One section per edit. Wait for confirmation before proceeding.
- If a change breaks the layout, revert immediately and report.

## When In Doubt
- Preserve what exists. Only refine what is explicitly mapped above.
- If a selector is not listed here, do not change it.
- If uncertain about a value, flag it and ask — do not guess.
- Check DESIGN.md section 9 for exact token values.
